## 2026-04-03 - Find & Replace across all sets registers undo only for completed sets
- Root cause: when user cancels mid-loop, `apiFetch` with an in-flight request throws an AbortError that propagated to the outer catch block, bypassing the undo registration code entirely — even though sets that completed before the abort had their tokens renamed on the server.
- Fix: wrapped each `apiFetch` call inside the per-set loop in a try/catch; AbortErrors convert to `wasAborted = true; break` so the loop exits cleanly and post-loop undo registration always runs.
- After undo registration, if `wasAborted` and `totalRenamed > 0`, show a partial success message ("Cancelled — renamed N tokens in K of M sets") and call `onRefresh`, then `return` to skip the full-success dialog-close path.

