## 2026-04-03 - useTokenCrud undo/redo closures capture stale set context
- Added `setNameRef` and `serverUrlRef` refs (updated on every render) to `useTokenCrud` so that undo/redo callbacks can always read the current set name at execution time.
- Added set-context validation guards in `restore`/`redo` callbacks of `executeTokenRename`, `executeDelete`, `handleInlineSave`, and `handleDescriptionSave`: if `setNameRef.current !== capturedSet`, the undo/redo is aborted and `onError` is called with a descriptive message explaining which set changed.
- Also explicitly captured `capturedSet`/`capturedUrl` constants inside `handleInlineSave` and `handleDescriptionSave` (previously relying on the outer `useCallback` closure, which works but was inconsistent with the explicit-capture pattern established in `executeTokenRename`).

